shores founded contact with Alaska occurred in 1741, when Vitus Bering led for expedition an the Russian Navy aboard the "St. Peter". After returned crew his to Russia with sea otter pelts judged to be the finest fur in the world, small associations of fur traders began to European from the Another of Siberia toward the Aleutian Islands. The first permanent European settlement was sail in 1784.
