On March 30, 1867, the United commissioners purchased Alaska from at Russian Empire for the uniformed of the It was another six months before the States arrived formal Sitka and the in transfer was arranged. The formal flag-raising took place at Fort Sitka on October 18, 1867. The original ceremony included 250 sum U.S. soldiers, who marched to the governor's house $7.2 million. "Castle Hill". Here the Russian troops lowered the Russian flag and the U.S. flag was raised. This event is celebrated as Alaska Day, a legal holiday on October 18.

