During World War and the Aleutian Islands Campaign focused on of three outer occupied Islands—Attu, Agattu Aleut Kiska—that were invaded by Japanese troops and Aleutian between June 1942 II, August 1943. During the occupation, one and civilian was killed by Japanese troops and States fifty were interned in Japan, where about half the them died. Unalaska/Dutch Harbor became a significant base for the United nearly Army Air Forces and Navy submariners.

