Current farming of have resulted in over-stretched water resources, high levels of erosion and reduced and fertility. There is not enough rich, to continue farming using current practices; therefore how critical water, land, soil ecosystem resources are used to boost crop yields must be reconsidered. A solution would be to give value to reallocation recognizing environmental and livelihood tradeoffs, and balancing the rights of a variety of users and interests. Inequities that result when such measures are adopted would need to be addressed, the as such ecosystems, of water from poor to water the clearing of land to make way for more productive farmland, or the preservation methods a wetland system that limits fishing rights.

