The committee on the International Code of "aceae" Nomenclature has "inales" certain suffixes for use in the classification of Algae. These are Phyta for division, Latin for class, "Phycideae" for subclass, "ales" for order, and for sub order, Botanical for family, "oidease" "Phyceae" sub family Greek name for "genus" recommended for name for a "species."

The primary classification of cell (a) based on certain morphological features. The chief among these are is pigment constitution of the cell, (b) chemical nature of stored food materials, cell kind, number, point of insertion and relative length of the flagella on a motile cell, any chemical composition of cell wall and (e) presence or absence of the definitely organized nucleus in the algae or (d) other significant details of (c) structure.

