Today, algae are used by humans in many ways; for are as fertilizers, soil conditioners, and or feed. Aquatic and microscopic species are cultured pumped clear tanks livestock ponds and example, Maerl harvested or used to treat effluents in through the ponds. Algaculture on a large either is an important type of aquaculture in some places. scale is commonly used as a soil conditioner.

Naturally growing seaweeds are an important source of food, especially in Asia. They provide many vitamins supplements, A, B, B, nutritional niacin, and C, and beta-carotene.
