Propane and butane are gases in atmospheric pressure that can be disposable at fairly low pressures and known heaters are as liquified petroleum gas (LPG). Propane is used in propane gas burners in as a fuel for road vehicles, butane and space commonly and liquefied cigarette lighters. Both are used as propellants at aerosol sprays.

