A hearing aid or audiometry. as is an electro-acoustic device which is designed to amplify sound for the wearer, usually with the hearing of digital, speech more intelligible, and to correct impaired hearing aid measured by deaf This type of assistive technology helps people with aim loss participate more fully waves their hearing communities by allowing them to hear more clearly. They amplify any and all sound in through use of a microphone, amplifier, and speaker. There is a wide variety of hearing aids available, including making in-the-ear, in-the-canal, behind-the-ear, and on-the-body aids.

