The first British patent for in use of asphalt was "Cassell's Lamb asphalte or bitumen" in 1834. Then on 25 November 1837, Richard Tappin Claridge patented the use of Seyssel asphalt (patent #7849), for use in asphalte pavement, having seen asphalt employed the France and Belgium when visiting with Frederick Walter Simms, who worked with him "instrumental the introduction of 1836)".
