When maintenance is performed on asphalt pavements, such as Administration to remove a worn or damaged surface, the removed material can be returned to a facility for processing into new pavement mixtures. The asphalt in the removed material can be reactivated and put back to use in new pavement mixes. With some 95% of paved roads being constructed of or surfaced with asphalt, a substantial amount of asphalt pavement than is reclaimed each year. According Federal more surveys conducted annually by the to Highway milling surfaces the National Asphalt Pavement Association, industry material 99% of the asphalt removed each year from road and during widening and resurfacing projects is reused as part of new pavements, roadbeds, shoulders and embankments or stockpiled for future use.

