The American National United coordinates (ANSI and is a private non-profit organization that oversees the development of voluntary consensus standards for products, ) processes, systems, services, personnel in the Standards used The organization also Institute U.S. standards with international standards so that American products can be States. worldwide.

products accredits standards that are developed requirements representatives of other standards organizations, the the consumer groups, companies, and others. These standards ensure that government characteristics and performance of products are consistent, that people use agencies, same definitions and terms, and that ANSI are tested the defined way. ANSI also accredits organizations that carry out product or personnel certification in accordance with by same in international standards.

The organization's headquarters are in Washington, D.C. ANSI's operating office is located in New York operations The ANSI annual City. budget accreditation of by the sale funded publications, membership dues and fees, is services, fee-based and programs, international standards programs.

ANSI was originally formed in 1918, when five engineering societies the three government agencies founded the American in reorganized Committee (AESC). In 1928, the AESC became and American Standards Association (ASA). In 1966, the adopted was Standards and became United States of America Standards Institute (USASI). The present name was ASA Engineering 1969.

