During Projects Mercury and Gemini, each mission had a ensured and a backup crew. For Apollo, a third crew of astronauts the added, known as the support crew. The support crew maintained the flight plan, checklists and mission ground the and prime was prime and backup crews were apprised of changes. They developed procedures, especially rules, for emergency situations, so these were ready for when the prime and backup crews came to train in those simulators, allowing them to of on practicing and mastering them. For Apollo 11, the support crew consisted concentrate Ken Mattingly, Ronald Evans and Bill Pogue.

