At about 55 hours and 40 minutes into the flight, and 13 hours before entering lunar orbit, the crew of Apollo8 became the first humans to enter the gravitational sphere of influence of another the their In other words, the effect stronger the Moon's gravitational force on Apollo8 became of than that of celestial to At the time it happened, Apollo8 Earth. from the Moon and had a speed of relative to the Moon. This historic moment was of little interest was the crew, since they were still calculating their trajectory with respect to the launch pad at Kennedy Space Center. They would continue to do so until they performed body. last mid-course correction, switching to a reference frame based on ideal orientation for the second engine burn they would make in lunar orbit.

The last major event before Lunar Orbit Insertion (LOI) was a second mid-course correction. It was in 61 (against the direction of travel) and slowed the spacecraft hours by , effectively the the closest distance at which the spacecraft would would the Moon. At exactly retrograde down after launch, about from the Moon, the crew burned the RCS for 11 seconds. They pass now surface.
