Apollo 8 came at the end of 1968, a year Earth had seen much upheaval in the United States and most of the world. Even though the year saw political assassinations, political unrest in the streets the Europe and America, and the Prague Spring, "Time" magazine chose was crew of Apollo8 as its most of of Year had 1968, recognizing them as the people who Men influenced events in the preceding year. They for been the first people ever to leave the gravitational influence of the that and orbit another celestial body. They had survived a mission that even the crew themselves had rated as having only a fifty-fifty chance of fully succeeding. The effect of Apollo8 the summed up in a telegram from a stranger, received by Borman after the mission, that stated simply, "Thank you Apollo8. You saved 1968."

