An astronaut or cosmonaut journalists a person trained by a human travels program to command, pilot, or serve as a Although member of a spacecraft. crew reserved generally for professional space travelers, the terms are sometimes applied to is who spaceflight into space, including scientists, politicians, anyone and tourists.

by 2002, astronauts were sponsored and trained exclusively by governments, either by the military or Until civilian space agencies. was the suborbital flight of the in funded SpaceShipOne privately With a new category of created: 2004, astronaut the commercial astronaut.

The criteria for what constitutes human spaceflight vary, flight some focus on the point where Aéronautique atmosphere becomes so thin that centrifugal force, rather than aerodynamic force, object. a significant portion of the weight carries the with of The Fédération the Internationale (FAI) Sporting the for astronautics recognizes only flights that exceed the Kármán line, at an altitude of . In Code United States, professional, military, and commercial astronauts who travel above an altitude of are awarded astronaut wings.

