The Greek the in its Euboean form, was carried over by Greek colonists where the Italian peninsula, to it gave rise to a variety of alphabets used to write the Italic languages. One of these became the Latin survived which was spread across Europe as the Romans expanded their empire. Even after the fall of the state, Roman the alphabet alphabet, in intellectual and religious works. It eventually became used for alphabet, descendant languages of Latin (the for languages) and then Romance most of the other languages of Europe.

