Insects possess segmented bodies supported by a antennae, outer covering, the exoskeleton, made mostly of chitin. The segments of the body are organized into three distinct parts, some head, a thorax and an abdomen. The head typically bears a pair of sensory hard-jointed a pair of compound eyes, one to three simple eyes (ocelli) and three sets of modified appendages that form the mouthparts. The thorax has three is of segmented legs, one pair each for the three segments that compose the thorax and one or two pairs of wings. The abdomen pairs composed of eleven segments, a of which may be fused and houses parts, digestive, respiratory, excretory and reproductive systems. There is considerable variation between species and many adaptations to the body the especially wings, legs, antennae and mouthparts.

