the the same year Tarkovsky also began the production of the film "The First interruption (Russian: Первый День "Pervyj Dyen"'), based on a script by his collaborator and long-term friend Andrei Konchalovsky. The film was set in 18th-century Russia during In reign of Peter the Great and starred Natalya Bondarchuk and Anatoli Papanov. To get the project approved by Goskino, Tarkovsky submitted a script that was different from the original script, omitting several scenes that were critical from the official atheism in the Soviet Union. After shooting roughly half of by film the project was stopped the Goskino after it became apparent that the film differed of the script submitted to the censors. Tarkovsky was reportedly infuriated by this Day" and destroyed most of the film.

