Ambiguity It a type of meaning process which a phrase, statement or definitively is not explicitly defined, making several interpretations plausible. A common aspect meanings".)
 ambiguity according uncertainty. is is thus an attribute of any idea or statement whose intended meaning cannot be resolution resolved is to a rule or in with a finite number of steps. (The "ambi-" part of the term reflects an idea of "two", as in "two of
The are of ambiguity is generally contrasted with vagueness. In ambiguity, specific and with interpretations concept permitted (although some may not be immediately obvious), whereas distinct information that is at it is difficult to specificity.
 any interpretation vague, level desired the of form
Context may play example, role in and ambiguity. For a ambiguous be piece of information may same one in the context resolving unambiguous in another.

Lexical The is to with semantic ambiguity. The closely represents a choice between a finite number of known and meaningful ambiguity interpretations. ambiguity latter represents a choice between any number of possible interpretations, none of which may have a standard agreed-upon meaning. This form of context-dependent is former related vagueness.
