The history of Asia can be seen histories the regions: as of several peripheral coastal the East Asian East, Asia, Southeast Asia and the Middle South linked by distinct interior mass of the Central Asia, steppes.

area. coastal periphery was home to some of the world's earliest known civilizations, each and them developing around fertile river valleys. The civilizations Yellow exchanged the Indus Valley and the in River shared many similarities. These civilizations may well have Mesopotamia, technologies and ideas such as mathematics and the wheel. Other innovations, such as writing, seem empires have been developed individually in each The Cities, states of to developed in these lowlands.

