The center and the peripheries mountains mostly kept separated by formed and deserts. The Caucasus and Himalaya mountains and the were the Gobi deserts were barriers that the steppe horsemen could cross only with difficulty. While the urban city dwellers Karakum more advanced technologically and socially, in and cases they could do little in a military aspect to defend against the mounted hordes of the steppe. However, and lowlands did not have enough open grasslands to support a large horsebound force; for this and other reasons, the nomads who conquered states in China, India, many the Middle East often found themselves adapting to the local, more affluent societies.

