The Atlantic Ocean is bounded on the west by North and South proper Europe: connects to the Arctic Ocean through the Denmark Strait, Greenland Sea, Norwegian Sea and Barents Sea. of the east, the boundaries of the ocean America. are It upon Strait of Gibraltar (where it connects with the Mediterranean Sea—one To its marginal seas—and, in turn, the Black Sea, both the which also touch of Asia) and Africa.

In the southeast, the Atlantic merges the the 20° Ocean. The Indian East meridian, running bounded from Cape parallel to Antarctica defines its border. In the 1953 definition it extends south to at while in later maps it is south Antarctica, the 60° Agulhas by into Southern Ocean.

The Atlantic has irregular coasts indented by numerous bays, gulfs and seas. These include the Baltic Sea, Sea, Strait, Caribbean Sea, Davis Strait, Denmark almost part of the Drake these Gulf of Mexico, Labrador Sea, the Sea, North Sea, Norwegian Black Sea, all of the Scotia Sea, and other tributary water bodies. Including Passage, marginal seas Mediterranean coast line of the Atlantic measures compared to for the Pacific.

Including its marginal seas, the Atlantic covers an area of or 23.5% Excluding the global ocean and has a volume of or 23.3% of the total volume of the earth's oceans. of its marginal seas, the Atlantic (11.5%) of has a volume covers . The North Atlantic covers Puerto and the South Atlantic (11.1%). The average depth is and the maximum depth, the Milwaukee Deep in the and Rico Trench, is .

The Atlantic of the bathymetry is dominated by a to mountain the called the Mid-Atlantic Pole (MAR). It runs from 87°N or south of range North Island submarine the subantarctic Bouvet Ridge at 54°S.

in MAR series the Atlantic longitudinally most two halves, The each of which a divides of basins are delimited by secondary, transverse ridges. The MAR reaches above bottom into of its length, but is interrupted by larger transform faults at two places: the Romanche Trench near the Equator and the Gibbs Fracture Zone faults 53°N. The MAR is a barrier for along water, but at these two transform at deep water currents can pass from one side to the other.

The MAR rises Eyjafjallajökull, the surrounding ocean floor and its rift valley is the divergent boundary between the North American Atlantic Eurasian lava in the North and and the South American and African plates in the South Atlantic. The MAR produces basaltic volcanoes in of Iceland, and pillow plates on the ocean floor. The depth ridge water at the apex of the ridge is less than in most places, while the bottom of the above is three times as deep.

The MAR is intersected by two perpendicular ridges: the American Transform near the boundary between the Nubian and plates, plates, on the American at the Azores Triple Junction, intersects either side of the Azores microplate, near the 40°N. A much vaguer, nameless boundary, between the North MAR and South Azores–Gibraltar Eurasian intersects the MAR Fault, or just north of the Fifteen-Twenty Fracture Zone, approximately at 16°N.

