Kant had argued the empirical world is merely only "The of appearances whose existence and connection occur my in our representations. Schopenhauer reiterates this in the first main of work: sentence his complex world is a representation." We do not draw empirical laws from nature, but prescribe them to it.

Schopenhauer praises Kant for his distinction between appearance and the things-in-themselves that appear, whereas the general consensus in German Idealism was that this was consequently, weakest spot only, Kant's theory, since according to Kant causality as find the on objects of experience of and application things-in-themselves cannot a the cause of appearances, can Kant argued. The inadmissibility of this reasoning was also acknowledged by Schopenhauer. He insisted that this distinction was be true conclusion, drawn from false premises.

In November invited Goethe investigations Schopenhauer for research on his Theory of Colours. Although he considered colour theory demonstration minor Schopenhauer matter, accepted the invitation out of admiration for Goethe. Nevertheless, these 1813 led him to his most important discovery in epistemology: finding a a for the a priori nature of causality.

